title: Supplement company correspondence (Food And Drug Administration, Office Of Regulatory Affairs)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Email or letters containing warning letters, recall requests, 483s, or untitled letters between FDA's CDER or ORA and the following companies referencing yellow oleander contamination in supplements between January 1, 2023 to December 31, 2025

OBC Group, SdB Semilla de Brasil Tejocote Root, SdB ELITE, natural vida, SiluetaYa LLC, New Me, Shopnewmeroot.com, vidaslim co., vidaslim USA, Creativa Interiors, LLC, Privit Wellness, LLC, Innovacion Natural, LLC, World Green Nutrition Inc., Alipotec, Alipotec South TX, NWL Nutra, Global Mix Inc., Eva Nutrition, Sunset Sales +, ELV King, ALIPOTEC RAIZ DE TEJOCOTE, Natural Supplements, LLC, Science of Alpha, H and Natural, H & Natural, Backstage CTC Seller, Nutraholics ELV, Niwali, or Pastor-Villareal, Inc.

I am an investigative journalist writing for MedShadow.org.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emma Yasinski

title: Digital Asset Reports On Strategic Reserve Executive Order

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

reports and/or accounting received by the Treasury on the accounting of all Government digital assets in the possession of each federal agency as ordered in the Executive Order "ESTABLISHMENT OF THE STRATEGIC BITCOIN RESERVE AND UNITED STATES DIGITAL ASSET STOCKPILE" dated March 5th, 2025, stating: "the head of each agency shall provide the Secretary of the Treasury [...] with a full accounting of all Government Digital Assets in such agency’s possession".

I am additionally requesting the confirmation of agencies that hold no digital assets, as ordered: "If such agency holds no Government Digital Assets, such agency shall confirm such fact to the Secretary of the Treasury."

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Lola Leetz

title: FOIA Processing Logs (Immigration and Customs Enforcement)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting a copy of the FOIA request logs for your agency covering the period from January 1st, 2026 through whenever this request is ultimately processed.  I request that these logs include the following fields for each entry: 
1. The tracking number assigned to the request.
2. The date the request was received.
3. The name of the requester and associated organization, if specified.
4. A description or summary of the records requested.
5. The status of the request (e.g., pending, closed, partially granted, denied).
6. The final disposition and the specific FOIA exemptions cited, if applicable.

I request that these records be provided in an electronic, searchable format, such as a CSV file, to minimize costs and facilitate review. I am an individual researcher, and this request is made for non-commercial purposes. 
Thank you for your assistance.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emma Lehman
